 />\n<br />\nPublished 15 March 2018<br />\nFrom:<br />\nPrime Minister's Office, 10 Downing Street and The Rt Hon Theresa May MP"},{"pid":"123751b70fef52a5828a4ad938baf69806381702","tid":594144,"uid":147314,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"quote":{"pid":"3b18ae9c43200752f47ac0e7f35858f5e94a98c6","tid":594144,"uid":147314,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"866903393f8c4b2ff92efcf6925d780666925974","tid":594144,"uid":36178,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:12:13.000Z","msg":"原版四國聲明？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:18:59.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/salisbury-attack-joint-statement-from-the-leaders-of-france-germany-the-united-states-and-the-united-kingdom\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Fsalisbury-attack-joint-statement-from-the-leaders-of-france-germany-the-united-states-and-the-united-kingdom&d=3CbmPWHc0YoSZgGaxrV5U57TfgnX9jywtYe9GXZmhCU%3D&h=14861e23\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/salisbury-attack-joint-statement-from-the-leaders-of-france-germany-the-united-states-and-the-united-kingdom</a><br />\n<br />\nSalisbury attack: Joint statement from the leaders of France, Germany, the United States and the United Kingdom<br />\n<br />\nThe leaders of France, Germany, the United States and the United Kingdom have issued the following joint statement on the attack which took place in Salisbury, UK.<br />\n<br />\nPublished 15 March 2018<br />\nFrom:<br />\nPrime Minister's Office, 10 Downing Street and The Rt Hon Theresa May MP"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:19:12.000Z","msg":"We, the leaders of France, Germany, the United States and the United Kingdom, abhor the attack that took place against Sergei and Yulia Skripal in Salisbury, UK, on 4 March 2018. A British police officer who was also exposed in the attack remains seriously ill, and the lives of many innocent British citizens have been threatened. We express our sympathies to them all, and our admiration for the UK police and emergency services for their courageous response.<br />\n<br />\nThis use of a military-grade nerve agent, of a type developed by Russia, constitutes the first offensive use of a nerve agent in Europe since the Second World War. It is an assault on UK sovereignty and any such use by a State party is a clear violation of the Chemical Weapons Convention and a breach of international law. It threatens the security of us all.<br />\n<br />\nThe United Kingdom briefed thoroughly its allies that it was highly likely that Russia was responsible for the attack. We share the UK assessment that there is no plausible alternative explanation, and note that Russia&acute;s failure to address the legitimate request by the UK government further underlines its responsibility. We call on Russia to address all questions related to the attack in Salisbury. Russia should in particular provide full and complete disclosure of the Novichok programme to the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW)."},{"pid":"26d59d21e537aa91aa1f5ec9447961ceeaba7bd1","tid":594144,"uid":147314,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"123751b70fef52a5828a4ad938baf69806381702","tid":594144,"uid":147314,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"quote":{"pid":"3b18ae9c43200752f47ac0e7f35858f5e94a98c6","tid":594144,"uid":147314,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"866903393f8c4b2ff92efcf6925d780666925974","tid":594144,"uid":36178,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:12:13.000Z","msg":"原版四國聲明？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:18:59.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/salisbury-attack-joint-statement-from-the-leaders-of-france-germany-the-united-states-and-the-united-kingdom\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Fsalisbury-attack-joint-statement-from-the-leaders-of-france-germany-the-united-states-and-the-united-kingdom&d=3CbmPWHc0YoSZgGaxrV5U57TfgnX9jywtYe9GXZmhCU%3D&h=14861e23\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/salisbury-attack-joint-statement-from-the-leaders-of-france-germany-the-united-states-and-the-united-kingdom</a><br />\n<br />\nSalisbury attack: Joint statement from the leaders of France, Germany, the United States and the United Kingdom<br />\n<br />\nThe leaders of France, Germany, the United States and the United Kingdom have issued the following joint statement on the attack which took place in Salisbury, UK.<br />\n<br />\nPublished 15 March 2018<br />\nFrom:<br />\nPrime Minister's Office, 10 Downing Street and The Rt Hon Theresa May MP"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:19:12.000Z","msg":"We, the leaders of France, Germany, the United States and the United Kingdom, abhor the attack that took place against Sergei and Yulia Skripal in Salisbury, UK, on 4 March 2018. A British police officer who was also exposed in the attack remains seriously ill, and the lives of many innocent British citizens have been threatened. We express our sympathies to them all, and our admiration for the UK police and emergency services for their courageous response.<br />\n<br />\nThis use of a military-grade nerve agent, of a type developed by Russia, constitutes the first offensive use of a nerve agent in Europe since the Second World War. It is an assault on UK sovereignty and any such use by a State party is a clear violation of the Chemical Weapons Convention and a breach of international law. It threatens the security of us all.<br />\n<br />\nThe United Kingdom briefed thoroughly its allies that it was highly likely that Russia was responsible for the attack. We share the UK assessment that there is no plausible alternative explanation, and note that Russia&acute;s failure to address the legitimate request by the UK government further underlines its responsibility. We call on Russia to address all questions related to the attack in Salisbury. Russia should in particular provide full and complete disclosure of the Novichok programme to the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW)."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:20:14.000Z","msg":"Our concerns are also heightened against the background of a pattern of earlier irresponsible Russian behaviour. We call on Russia to live up to its responsibilities as a member of the UN Security Council to uphold international peace and security."},{"pid":"da5eb4ec327abef61c96e873a3e9908915ab7dc8","tid":594144,"uid":75326,"like":1,"dislike":23,"score":-22,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:24:14.000Z","msg":"鬼鬼地，有冇可能真係唔關俄羅斯事?<br />\n依家又正係俄國總統大選、6月又黎世界杯<br />\n俄佬為乜要搞呢潭嘢? 普京落唔到臺"},{"pid":"3d824be35d39e5860bdc30da4076a726d11ec803","tid":594144,"uid":132038,"like":5,"dislike":13,"score":-8,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:25:02.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"dc8b23f6b96bf619b993fcec439c2e32c6f56de2","tid":594144,"uid":30169,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"3908e198b0e44a1a1330a798df8c2f342ca01300","tid":594144,"uid":37735,"like":53,"dislike":1,"score":52,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:07:40.000Z","msg":"拉隊走人 唔踢世界盃<br />\n<br />\n等俄羅斯 搞世盃的錢燒哂去<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:25:46.000Z","msg":"呢個夠絕"},{"pid":"672515189e2e28d4c5661c45fdaea3a621ca6617","tid":594144,"uid":76216,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"quote":{"pid":"3d824be35d39e5860bdc30da4076a726d11ec803","tid":594144,"uid":132038,"like":5,"dislike":13,"score":-8,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:25:02.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-15T15:27:26.000Z","msg":"sorry  北韓係小早川秀秋 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e31d9eb21b27c6aeedf0d1b127d0798ae736aec1","tid":594144,"uid":30169,"like":14,"dislike":0,"score":14,"quote":{"pid":"3d824be35d39e5860bdc30da4076a726d11ec803","tid":594144,"uid":132038,"like":5,"dislike":13,"sco